-- China Hasn’t Stopped Airlines From Buying Airbus Planes: CAAC
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-03-10T07:12:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-10/china-hasn-t-barred-airlines-from-buying-airbus-jets-aviation-chief-says.html
The Chinese government hasn’t
issued any mandate forbidding the nation’s airlines from buying
Airbus SAS planes and won’t dictate the carriers’ purchases,
said  Li Jiaxiang , head of the Civil Aviation Administration of
 China .  The government encourages airlines to buy planes based on
costs savings and increasing reliability and safety, Li said in
an interview.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
